Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Kunitzin-RE (natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals, UCSS1a; BBL)

Literature Information.Literature: APD analysis reveals that the sequence of THE PEPTIDE shows 94.1% similarity toAndersonin-W2.Activity: Active against E. coli (MIC 30 uM). A change of the last K to F reduced activity (MIC 160 uM). CKAAFC itself is not antimicrobial. The peptide contains a canonical Kunitz-type protease inhibitor motif (-CKAAFC-), thereby named as kunitzins. RE is the abbreviation of the frog Latin name. Effective inhibitor of trypsin with a Ki 5.5 uM.
Literature Information.Author: Chen X, Wang H, Shen Y, Wang L, Zhou M, Chen T, Shaw C.2016
Literature Information.Title: Kunitzins: Prototypes of a new class of protease inhibitor from the skin secretions of European and Asian frogs
